Immunologic reactivity of the body and clinico-roentgenological picture of acute pneumonia in adults. There was No correlation between the state of immunological reactivity in patients with acute pneumonia and the nature of infiltration of the pulmonary tissue (focal, confluent). Indices characterizing the cellular and humoral immunity links, were, to a large extent, related to a course of disease (complicated, uncomplicated). The most significant changes in the immune status were noted inn patients with acute pneumonia developing in the presence of chronic bronchitis.